<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1261.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 7, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>. Your despatch of the 19th ultimo, No. 857,
                            has been received. Your proceedings, related therein, are approved. It
                            is left entirely to your discretion to decide upon the course to be
                            pursued in regard to the prosecutions to which you refer.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>. <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>